# Zirikly, Sharansky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Zirikly (; , Yerekle) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Ziriklinsky Selsoviet, Sharansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 835 as of 2010. There are 7 streets.
Geography
Zirikly is located 21&nbsp;km northwest of Sharan (the district's administrative centre) by road. Sharlykbash is the nearest rural locality.
